			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ND or CA?<a name="24220"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 27 04 6:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well I just had a closer look at your AAs and stuff.
<br />

<br />
My real suggestion for you (well basically that is what I did back in the time):
<br />
Get following AAs
<br />
MC1-&gt;CA1-&gt;CS1-&gt;ND1-&gt;PE
<br />

<br />
Why?
<br />
MC1: well you have FM and only FT1 so far. That means you regen 2 mana per tic (I hope<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />). That's a whooping 45 minutes to recover the 900 mana of a FM. With even 1 more mana regen you cut that time by 33% to 30 miutes per FM. 
<br />

<br />
CA1/CS1/ND1: The first levels in those archabilities provide a benefit of 2% for 2AA. The second levels come at 4AA for 3%, the third levels come at 6AA for 5%.
<br />

<br />
But it gets even better. PE adds 2% to each of those 3 for 5 AAs. That would be 1.67 AA for 2% in each ability.
<br />

<br />
So...you could get CA3 for 12 AA and 10% benefit.
<br />
Or...you could get 4% CA, 4% CS and 4% ND for 11 AA.
<br />

<br />
You won't get any defensive abilities any cheaper.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
