				<td colspan="2"><span>SCF all the way!!
<br />

<br />
Ok, just kidding.  Yes, I got SCF3 before ND3 and even before CA3.  But I nuke (chain-Scream) alot and I love procs.  When soloing stuff that summons, I just Slow it with Requime and then melee away chain-Screaming (Mez / SS BP heal as necessary).  I have HA5, Ambidex, and pretty decent weapons but let me tell you..  Scream DPS owns my melee DPS.  And there's just something satisfying about seeing those big (for Bards) spell crits.  I <i>love</i> SCF3.
<br />

<br />
That said.  I'm going to have to say that CA is the best of the bunch.  I've got LR5 now, but even with just CA3 the amount of misses was just insane.  That's a lot of healer mana saved if you're pulling, and probably the difference between life and bind point if for some reason you were getting smacked on a raid.  I love CA.
<br />

<br />
ND3 is nice but spending AA points on *just* HP upgrade didn't thrill me.  Felt more like grinding out exp to fulfill an obligation than it did having fun and buying useful skill upgrades.  I was glad when that 12pt AA was over with.
<br />
And I once survived a raid encounter with nasty AE, dropping to 60 HP at one point before catching a heal...  This AA saved muh life. =)</span></td>
