			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ND or CA?<a name="25651"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 5 04 7:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Increases the player’s base hitpoints. (The percentages are based off your base hitpoints, which include stamina and stamina effects.)</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Precisely the point. It works off your base hp, including stamina and stamina effects.
<br />

<br />
It does NOT include raw hp gear, and so your argument that the effect scales with better gear is only valid until stamina is capped (including any buffs). Once stamina is maxed, you'll get no extra benefit from ND by getting more hp gear. Its still a great AA though.
<br />

<br />
To the original question, I'd say it depends.
<br />

<br />
To you take more damage from AEs and spells, or from mobs meleeing you (e.g. you chain pull and offtank until tank takes it off you)? If you raid a lot, its likely to be the former and I'd take ND3 first. If you don't raid so much but you do a lot of pulling and get knocked about quite a bit, then CA3.
<br />

<br />
In the longer term get both anyway <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />I'd also get MC1, its great value for money, and consider what others have said about working to PE too.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
